Other Measures 4


1. Right click on "countries-aggregated" and click "New measure"

2. Input the DAX formulas for 4 individual new measures  


Recovered:

.Recovered Rate = CALCULATE(

    DIVIDE([.CA Recovered], [.CA Confirmed], 0),

    'countries-aggregated'[Date]) + 0

 

Recovered WoW% = VAR __PreviousWeek = DIVIDE(MAX('countries-aggregated'[lastWeekTotalRecovered]),
MAX('countries-aggregated'[lastWeekTotalCases]),0)

Return
DIVIDE(([.RecoveredRate]- __PreviousWeek),__PreviousWeek,0)+0

 

Death:



.DeathRate = CALCULATE(

    DIVIDE([.CA Death], [.CA Confirmed], 0), 

    'countries-aggregated'[Date]

 ) + 0

 

 

 .Death WoW% = VAR __PreviousWeek = DIVIDE(MAX('countries-aggregated'[lastWeekTotalDeaths]),MAX('countries-aggregated'[lastWeekTotalCases]),0)
Return
DIVIDE(([.Death Rate]- __PreviousWeek),__PreviousWeek,0)+0

 


3. You should now have 4 measures indicating Rate and WoW%





Date Concatenations


1) Click to on the left-hand side to your 'Data' icon 

2) Click New Column

3) Input the formula for 4 individual New Columns (WeekStart, WeeksEnd, WeekDuration, Last Twelve Weeks)


 WeekStart = 'Date'[Date] - WEEKDAY('Date'[Date], 1) + 1


 WeeksEnd = 'Date'[Date] - WEEKDAY('Date'[Date], 1) + 7


 WeekDuration = FORMAT('Date'[WeekStart], "M/D") & " " & "-" & " " & FORMAT('Date'[WeeksEnd], "M/D")


 Last Twelve Weeks =
VAR __a = MAX('Date'[WeeksEnd]) - 77
RETURN
IF('Date'[WeeksEnd] >= __a, "Last Twelve Weeks", "Other Weeks")
